Fabrication EngineerAdd to Jobs BasketYou can apply for up to 10 jobs at once by adding them to your basket.Application LimitCandidates can apply for up to 150 jobs in 28 days.
> Status: LiveParticipate in and advise on all fabrication and onshore construction activities and initiatives, including planning and scheduling, provision of training/inductions, documentation reviews etc.
•	Monitor the assigned construction scope to ensure EPC1 Contractor performs all work to agreed standards for Safety, Health and Environment and demonstrate a commitment to attaining high levels of HSE (Health, Safety & Environment) performance.
•	Establish and maintain effective team working with EPC1 Contractor to ensure the work is performed safely to the agreed schedule and to an acceptable standard.Job DetailsLocation:
> Salary: Tax Free / NegotiableWorking Locations: OfficePosted: 30/04/2014 07:43:00Expires: 07/05/2014 07:43:00Key Requirements
Minimum Requirements:
•	B.Sc. or equivalent degree in Engineering.
•	Minimum of 10 years of relevant experience in Oil and Gas industry (offshore/onshore) with comprehensive hands-on experience in Construction Engineering
•	Good HSE awareness and commitment
•	Good written and verbal communication skills
•	Good technical team and interpersonal skillsJob Description
Promote HSE awareness and ensure that all Client's Project HSE requirements are implemented and adhered to.
•	Provide effective and practical construction input to ensure constructability aspects of project execution are adequately considered.
•	Facilitate EPC-1 design engineering engagement during the construction preparation and execution.
•	Ensure that construction hazards and risks are fully considered by Contractor and that the appropriate mitigation and actions are implemented during the fabrication phase.
•	Ensure, through review and monitoring, that the construction schedule is achievable and that early mitigation of slippage or use of opportunities is identified and appropriate action taken.
•	Ensure that fabrication quality is maintained at an acceptable level, including all required records and tests; thus ensuring that assembly and readiness for load-out are achieved
•	Co-ordinate with all project stakeholders to facilitate the project execution with minimum disruption and hazards to both on-going operations and the EPC1 Contractor, i.e. interface and SIMOPS.
•	Liaise with the EPC1 Contractor and other IPMT groups to ensure timely and effective release of construction data/drawings and resolution of problems.
•	Ensure that efficient and effective communications are maintained between the EPC1 Contractor and IPMT, ensuring that all reporting requirements are met.
•	Develop close working relationships between fabrication and construction team members, HSE, QA/QC and Logistics teams to provide a consistent approach and effective resolution of issues. Encourage the same degree of co-operation within the EPC1 Contractor organization.
•	Develop a good team spirit within assigned IPMT personnel.
